                  break;
              case WEDNESDAY:
                  System.out.println("It's Wednesday");
                  break;
              default:
                  System.out.println("Other day");
          }
      }
  }
  ```

- **Advantages of Enums in Java:**
  - Type safety: Enums provide type safety by restricting variables to a predefined set of constants.
  - Readability: Enums make the code more readable and maintainable by giving meaningful names to constants.
  - Enum constants can be used in switch-case statements.

- **Use Cases:**
  - Enums are commonly used to represent a fixed set of constants such as days of the week, months, status codes, etc.
  - Enums can also be used in singleton pattern implementation, strategy pattern, and state machine design.

